						<summary>

						<p>Same wall.</p>						

						<p><hi rend="bold">Kulōttuṅga-chōḷadēva I: Year 45 = 1114-15 A.D.</hi></p>						

						<p>This inscription records a gift of a <hi rend="italic">sandhyā</hi> lamp to the temple of the god Tiruvālakkōyiluḍaiya Mahādēvar of Tirukkachchūr <hi rend="italic">alias</hi> Nittavinōdanallūr, by Amarkaḷa-nāyakan, a Vēḷān. Three cows gifted by him to meet the expenses of the lamp were accepted by four <hi rend="italic">Śivabrāhmaṇas,</hi> having right to worship in the temple, who had agreed to carry out, perpetually, the object of the gift. </p>						

						</summary>
